      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:41:5",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ حَمَلَ مَتَاعاً عَلَى رَأْسِهِ فَأَصَابَ إِنْسَاناً فَمَاتَ أَوِ انْكَسَرَ مِنْهُ فَقَالَ هُوَ ضَامِنٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Abu Nasr, from Dawood Bin Sirhan, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding a man who carried provisions upon his head, so they struck a human being and he died, or something broke from him. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He is responsible’."
        ]
      }
